This paper deals with the problem of determining whether a graph admits a tree $t$-spanner of diameter at most $t+1$, which is a problem related to graph theory and algorithms. The paper presents an efficient algorithm to determine graphs that admit a tree 3-spanner of diameter at most 5, which suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Graph Theory (cs.GT), or Numerical Analysis (cs.NA).
